==English==

===Etymology===
{{named-after|en|Charles Ponzi|wplink==|born=1882|died=1949|occ=con artist}}, who famously conducted a [[pyramid scheme]] in [[North America]] in the early twentieth century.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[fraudulent]] [[scheme]] where earlier [[investor]]s are paid with the money taken from new investors, giving the [[impression]] that the scheme is a [[viable]] [[investment]].
#: {{syn|en|Ponzi scam}}
#: {{cot|en|pyramid scheme}}
